articles.title: Australia hosts largest-ever military exercise with 19 nations, likely to draw Chinese attention - AP News
articles.description: Australia is hosting its largest-ever military drills, Exercise Talisman Sabre, involving over 35,000 personnel from 19 nations. The event began with live-fire exercises, including Australia’s first use of U.S.-supplied HIMARS rocket systems. The drills, held…
articles.content:
